description:
Currently, flake.nix must override the entire registry to add custom packages. This causes duplication since all default registry entries must be repeated.

Add a registry extension mechanism to allow extending the default registry rather than replacing it:

```nix
turnkey.toolchains = {
  # Only specify additions, not the full registry
  registryExtensions = {
    beads = inputs.beads.packages.${system}.default;
    mdbook = pkgs.mdbook;
  };
};
```

The flake-parts module should merge:
1. Default registry (nix/registry/default.nix)
2. User's registryExtensions
3. tw wrappers overlay (if enabled)

This reduces duplication and makes it easier to add new tools.
